flowRoot.flowPara: D10~D13 are used as SPI interface to make the shield communicate with Arduino
Digital Pins D11~D13&D4 will be occupied by the MicroSD Module
Arduino uses D10~D13 (SPI) to communicate with the W5100 on the ethernet shield and these pins cannot be used for general I/O
Instruction for Digital Pin 2 To 7 and 10 To 13
